ames.com/popular/1/England+and+Wales/2001 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in England and Wales (2001)}}</ref> || 37th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/Ireland/2001 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in Ireland (2001)}}</ref> || * || 7th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/Scotland/2001 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in Scotland (2001)}}</ref> || 4th\n| *\n|-\n| 2000 || 53rd<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/England+and+Wales/2000 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in England and Wales (2000)}}</ref> || 31st<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/Ireland/2000 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in Ireland (2000)}}</ref> || * || 6th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/Scotland/2000 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in Scotland (2000)}}</ref> || 7th\n| *\n|-\n| 1999 || 46th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/England+and+Wales/1999 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in England and Wales (1999)}}</ref> || 28th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/Ireland/1999 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in Ireland (1999)}}</ref> || * || 7th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/Scotland/1999 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in Scotland (1999)}}</ref> || 4th\n| *\n|-\n| 1998 || 40th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/England+and+Wales/1998 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in England and Wales (1998)}}</ref> || 23rd<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/Ireland/1998 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in Ireland (1998)}}</ref> || * || 8th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/Scotland/1998 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in Scotland (1998)}}</ref> || 5th\n| *\n|-\n| 1997 || * || * || * || * || 1st\n| 10th\n|-\n| 1996 || * || * || * || * || 3rd\n| *\n|-\n| 1995 || * || * || 6th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://baby2see.com/names/topboysnamesscotlandireland.html |title=Most Popular Boys Baby Names in Northern Ireland, Scotland and Wales}}</ref> || * || 2nd\n| *\n|}\n\n=== United States ===\nThe eleventh most common baby name in 2006,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.babycenter.com/general/1506831.html |title=Top 100 Names of 2006}}</ref> Andrew was among the ten most popular names for male infants in 2005.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ssa.gov/OACT/babynames/ |title=Popular baby names |publisher=United States Social Security Administration}}</ref> Andrew was the sixth most popular choice for a male infant in 2004.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.canada.com/topics/lifestyle/parenting/story.html?id=29817ed5-5a13-4297-9e19-e152aa86078b&k=25431 |title=Emily, Jacob remain popular baby names |publisher=[[Canada.com]]}}</ref> In 2002 and 2001, Andrew was the seventh most popular baby name in the United States.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.socialsecurity.gov/pressoffice/pr/baby-names-pr.htm |title=Social Security Administration Delivers Most Popular Baby Names for 2002 |publisher=United States Social Security Administration}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.popularbabynames.com/cgi-bin/show_page.pl?fpage=a_02_babynames |title=Top 10 names of 2002 in USA |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070930105501/http://www.popularbabynames.com/cgi-bin/show_page.pl?fpage=a_02_babynames |archivedate=2007-09-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.popularbabynames.com/cgi-bin/show_page.pl?fpage=a_01_babynames |title=Top 10 names of 2001 in USA |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070930105514/http://www.popularbabynames.com/cgi-bin/show_page.pl?fpage=a_01_babynames |archivedate=2007-09-30}}</ref> In the 1980s, Andrew was the 19th most popular choice of baby name in the United States.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.babycenter.com/babyname/names80.html |title=BabyCenter 1980s \u2013 Most Popular Names}}</ref> In the 1970s it was the 31st most popular name.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.babycenter.com/babyname/names70.html |title=BabyCenter 1970s \u2013 Most Popular Names}}</ref> From the 1960s stretching back at least as far as the 1880s, Andrew was not among the forty most popular names in America.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.babycenter.com/babyname/names60.html |title=BabyCenter 1960s \u2013 Most Popular Names}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.babycenter.com/babyname/names50.html |title=BabyCenter 1950s \u2013 Most Popular Names}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.babycenter.com/babyname/names40.html |title=BabyCenter 1940s \u2013 Most Popular Names}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.babycenter.com/babyname/names30.html |title=BabyCenter 1930s \u2013 Most Popular Names}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.babycenter.com/babyname/names20.html |title=BabyCenter 1920s \u2013 Most Popular Names}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.babycenter.com/babyname/names10.html |title=BabyCenter 1910s \u2013 Most Popular Names}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.babycenter.com/babyname/names00.html |title=BabyCenter 1900s \u2013 Most Popular Names}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.babycenter.com/babyname/names1890.html |title=BabyCenter 1890s \u2013 Most Popular Names}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thenewparentsguide.com/most-popular-baby-names-1880.htm |title=Most Popular Baby Names for Boys and Girls in the 1880s |publisher=the New Parents' Guide |access-date=2007-04-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20020614124128/http://www.thenewparentsguide.com/most-popular-baby-names-1880.htm |archive-date=2002-06-14 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n== Variants by language ==\n* \u0d05\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d2f\u0d4b\u0d38\u0d4d: [[Malayalam language|Malayalam]], masculine\n* Andria: [[Georgian language|Georgian]], masculine\n* Aindrea, [[Aindreas]] or Anndra: [[Scottish Gaelic]], masculine\n* Aindr\u00e9as, Aindri\u00fa, Aindreas: [[Irish Gaelic]], masculine\n* [[Anaru (name)|Anaru]]: Maori, masculine\n* Andra: [[Scots language|Scots]], masculine\n* [[Ander]]: [[Basque language|Basque]], masculine\n* [[Anders]]: [[Danish language|Danish]], [[Finnish language|Finnish]], [[German language|German]], [[Norwegian language|Norwegian]], [[Swedish language|Swedish]], masculine\n* [[Andras]]: [[Welsh language|Welsh]]\n* [[Andr\u00e1s]], [[Endre (disambiguation)|Endre]]: [[Hungarian language|Hungarian]], masculine\n* [[Andra\u0161]]: [[Prekmurje dialect]] of Slovene, masculine\n* [[Andra\u017e]]: [[Slovene language|Slovene]], masculine\n* [[Andr\u00e9]] or Andre: [[French language|French]] and [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]], masculine\n* [[Andrea]]: [[Albanian language|Albanian]], [[Italian language|Italian]], [[Latin language|Latin]], masculine; [[Croatian language|Croatian]], [[Czech language|Czech]], [[Danish language|Danish]], [[English language|English]], [[Finnish language|Finnish]], [[Galician language|Galician]], [[German language|German]], [[Hungarian language|Hungarian]], [[Icelandic language|Icelandic]], [[Macedonian language|Macedonian]], [[Norwegian language|Norwegian]], [[Slovak language|Slovak]], [[Spanish language|Spanish]], [[Swedish language|Swedish]], feminine\n* [[Andreas]]: [[Armenian language|Armenian]], [[Cypriot Greek]], [[Danish language|Danish]], [[German language|German]], [[Greek language|Greek]], [[Norwegian language|Norwegian]], [[Icelandic language|Icelandic]], [[Swedish language|Swedish]], [[Welsh Language|Welsh]], masculine\n* [[Andreu (disambiguation)|Andreu]]: [[Catalan language|Catalan]], masculine\n* [[Andreea]]: [[Romanian language|Romanian]], feminine\n* [[Andr\u00e9e (given name)|Andr\u00e9e]]: [[French language|French]], feminine\n* [[Andrees]]: Older [[Dutch language|Dutch]] and seldom used [[Afrikaans]], masculine\n* [[Andrei (given name)|Andrei]]: [[Moldovan language|Moldovan]], [[Romanian language|Romanian]], [[Belarusian language|Belarusian]], [[Russian language|Russian]], masculine\n* [[Andreia]]: [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]], feminine\n* [[Andreina]]: [[Italian language|Italian]], feminine\n* [[Andris]]: [[Latvian language|Latvian]], masculine\n* [[Andrei (given name)|Andrei]]: [[Romanian language|Romanian]], masculine\n* [[Andrej]]: [[Belarusian language|Belarusian]], [[Croatian language|Croatian]], [[Macedonian language|Macedonian]], [[Serbian language|Serbian]], [[Slovak language|Slovak]], [[Slovene language|Slovene]], masculine\n* [[Andrey]]: [[Russian language|Russian]] and [[Bulgarian language|Bulgarian]], masculine (Cyrillic and thus often alternatively transliterated as Andrei for both)\n* [[Andreja]]: [[Macedonian language|Macedonian]], masculine; [[Croatian language|Croatian]], [[Slovene language|Slovene]], feminine\n* Andreo: [[Spanish language|Spanish]], masculine\n* [[Andres (name)|Andres]]: [[Estonian language|Estonian]], masculine\n* [[Andres (name)|Andr\u00e9s]]: [[Icelandic language|Icelandic]], [[Spanish language|Spanish]], masculine\n* Andressa: [[Brazilian Portuguese language|Portuguese]], feminine\n* Andreu: [[Catalan language|Catalan]], masculine\n* Andrew: [[English language|English]], masculine\n* [[Andric (given name)|Andric]]: [[English language|English]], masculine\n* [[Andries]]: [[Dutch language|Dutch]] and [[Afrikaans]], masculine\n* [[Andri]]: [[Icelandic language|Icelandic]], masculine\n* [[Andrii]]: [[Ukrainian language|Ukrainian]], masculine\n* [[Andrija]]: [[Croatian language|Croatian]] and [[Serbian language|Serbian]], masculine\n* [[Andrijana]]: [[Macedonian language|Macedonian]], [[Serbian language|Serbian]], feminine\n* [[Andris]], [[Andrejs]], An\u017eejs or [[And\u017eejs]]: [[Latvian language|Latvian]], masculine\n* [[Andrius]]: [[Lithuanian language|Lithuanian]], masculine\n* [[Andriy]]: [[Ukrainian language|Ukrainian]], masculine\n* [[Andrzej]] or [[J\u0119drzej]]: [[Polish language|Polish]], masculine\n* [[Andrzeja]]: [[Polish language|Polish]], feminine; obsolete\n* [[Antti]]: [[Finnish language|Finnish]], masculine\n* [[Ond\u0159ej]]: [[Czech language|Czech]], masculine\n* [[Ondrej]] or [[Andrej]]: [[Slovak language|Slovak]], masculine\n* [[Andrij]]: [[Ukrainian language|Ukrainian]], masculine\n* [[Indr\u00ec (name)|Indr\u00ec]] or [[Andrija]]: [[Maltese language|Maltese]], masculine\n* Andis, Andijs or Endijs: [[Latvian language|Latvian]], masculine\n* In [[Albanian language|Albanian]]: [[Andrea]], Andreu, Andr\u00e9, Ndr\u00e9, Ndreu, And\u00ebr, And\u00ebrs, masculine\n* \uc564\ub4dc\ub958: [[Korean language|Korean]], masculine\n* \u30a2\u30f3\u30c7\u30eb\u30fc: [[Japanese language|Japanese]], masculine\n* \u5b89\u5fb7\u9c81: [[Mandarin Chinese]] (simplified), masculine\n* \u5b89\u5fb7\u9b6f: [[Mandarin Chinese]] (traditional), masculine\n* \u0623\u0646\u062f\u0631\u0627\u0648\u0633 \"Andar\u0101wus\": [[Arabic language|Arabic]], masculine (or \u0623\u0646\u062f\u0631\u064a\u0647 \"Andrayh\" from French, or \u0623\u0646\u062f\u0631\u0648 \"Andr\u016b\" from English)\n* \u12a5\u1295\u12f5\u122a\u12eb\u1235: [[Amharic language|Amharic]], masculine\n''For alternate forms of Anna, see [[Anna (name)#Variant forms]]''\n\n== Notable people named Andrew ==\n=== Saint Andrew ===\nIn the Christian [[Bible]], [[Andrew the Apostle|Saint Andrew]] was the earliest disciple of [[Jesus]] and one of the twelve [[Apostles]].\n[[File:Apostol-Andrey-Pervozvannyj.jpg|right|120px|Saint Andrew]]\n\nOther saints named Andrew include:\n* Saint [[Andrew of Trier]] (d. 235), Bishop of Trier\n* Saint [[Andrew of Crete]], an 8th-century archbishop, theologian, homilist, and hymnographer\n* Saint [[Andrew of Crete (martyr)]]\n* Saint [[Andrew of Constantinople]]\n* Saints [[Andrew Dung-Lac]] An Tran, Andrew Thong Kim Nguyen, Andrew Trong Van Tram, and Andrew Tuong of the [[Vietnamese Martyrs]]\n* Saint [[Andrew Kim Taegon]] of the [[Korean Martyrs]]\n\n=== Kings Andrew ===\n* King [[Andrew I of Hungary]]\n* King [[Andrew II of Hungary]]\n* King [[Andrew III of Hungary]]\n\n=== Dukes Andrew ===\n* [[Andrius Algirdaitis]] (1325\u20131399), first son of [[Algirdas]]\n\n=== Princes Andrew ===\n* [[Prince Andrew, Duke of York]] (1960\u2013), second son of [[Elizabeth II of the United Kingdom|Elizabeth II]]\n* [[Prince Andrew of Greece and Denmark]] (1882\u20131944), the aforementioned's paternal grandfather and namesake\n* [[Edward VIII of the United Kingdom|Edward VIII]] (1894\u20131972) bore the name Andrew\n\n=== United States politics ===\n* [[Andrew Cuomo]] (56th Governor of New York)\n* [[Andrew Gillum]] (125th Mayor of Tallahassee, Florida)\n* [[Andrew Jackson]] (7th President of the United States of America)\n* [[Andrew Johnson]] (17th President of the United States of America)\n\n=== Business, culture, science, and sport ===\n* [[Andrew Abercromby]] \u2013 Scottish biomedical engineer and aquanaut\n* [[Andrew Bayes]] \u2013 American football player\n* [[Andrew Benintendi]] \u2013 Baseball player on the Boston Red Sox\n* [[Andy Biersack]] \u2013 lead vocalist of American rock band [[Black Veil Brides]]\n* [[Andrew Bayer]] \u2013 American DJ and Grammy-nominated record producer\n* [[Andrew Beck (American football)|Andrew Beck]] (born 1996) \u2013 American football player\n* [[Andrew Bird]] \u2013  American musician\n* [[Andrew Bloom]] \u2013 American Olympic shot putter\n* [[Andrew Bogut]] \u2013 Australian basketball player\n* [[Andrew Brown (American football)|Andrew Brown]] \u2013 American football player\n* [[Andrew Brunette]] \u2013 ice hockey player\n* [[Andrew Buckley (field hockey)|Andrew Buckley]] \u2013 field hockey player\n* [[Andrew Bynum]] \u2013 basketball player\n* [[Andrew Campbell (outfielder)]] - Australian professional baseball player\n* [[Andrew Carnegie]] \u2013 steel magnate and philanthropist\n* [[Andrew Colvin]] \u2013 Aussie police man and commissioner\n* [[Andrew Craig]] \u2013 keyboardist for The Nightrain\n* [[Andrew Dice Clay]] \u2013 comedian\n* [[Andrew Dost]] \u2013 Guitarist\n* [[Andrew Clayton]] \u2013 freestyle swimmer\n* [[Andrew Cole]] \u2013 footballer\n* [[Andrew Davenport]] (born 1965) \u2013 English actor, puppeteer, voice actor, music composer\n* [[Andrew Davies (writer)|Andrew Davies]] \u2013 screenwriter\n* [[Andy Dawson]] (born 1978) \u2013 English footballer\n* [[Andy Dawson (footballer, born 1979)|Andy Dawson]] (born 1979) \u2013 English footballer\n* [[Andrew De Silva]] (born 1974) \u2013 Sri Lankan Australian rock vocalist\n* [[Andrew Digby]] \u2014 an astronomer and ecologist whose work focusses on researching and conserving New Zealand's endangered endemic birds.\n* [[Andrew J. Feustel]] \u2013 American astronaut\n* [[Andrew Flintoff]] \u2013 cricketer\n* [[Andrew Rube Foster]] \u2013 Hall of Fame manager for baseball's [[Negro Leagues]]\n* [[Andrew Friedman]] \u2013 American, baseball general manager\n* [[Andrew Garfield]] \u2013 actor\n* [[Andrew Gaze]] \u2013 basketball player\n* [[Andy Gibb]] (Andrew Roy Gibb) \u2013 pop singer and composer\n* [[Andrew Gold]] (1951\u20132011) \u2013 American musician\n* [[Andrew Graham (disambiguation)|Andrew Graham]]\n* [[Andrew Graham-Dixon]] \u2013 art historian and broadcaster\n* [[Andy Griffith]] \u2013 actor/singer/comedian\n* [[Andrew Grove]] \u2013 businessman/engineer/author and a science pioneer\n* [[Andrew Hastie (field hockey)|Andrew Hastie]] \u2013 field hockey player\n* [[Andrew Hussie]] \u2013 artist at MSPAINTADVENTURES\n* [[Andrew Huxley]] \u2013 physiologist\n* [[Andrew Jacobs (journalist)|Andrew Jacobs]] \u2013 ''New York Times'' journalist, and documentary film director and producer\n* [[Andrew Jacobson]] \u2013 Major League Soccer player\n* [[Andrew Jayamanne]] \u2013 Sri Lankan film director\n* [[Andrew Johns]] \u2013 rugby league player\n* [[Andrew Johnson (English footballer)|Andrew Johnson]] \u2013 footballer\n* [[Andrew Johnston (Australian actor)|Andrew Johnston]] \u2013 actor\n* [[Andy Kaufman]] \u2013 comedian\n* [[Andrew Knott]] \u2013 English actor\n* [[Andrew Ladd]] \u2013 ice hockey player\n* [[Andrew Laine]] \u2013 American engineer\n* [[Andrew Lang]] \u2013 man of letters\n* [[Andrew Lee Potts]] \u2013 actor/director\n* [[Andrej Lemanis]] \u2013 Australian basketball coach\n* [[Andrew Lincoln]] \u2013 British actor\n* [[Andrew Lloyd Webber]] \u2013 composer and impresario\n* [[Andrew Lorraine]] \u2013 American baseball player\n* [[Andrew Luck]] \u2013 American football player\n* [[Andrew Luri]] \u2013 Sudanese-Australian actor\n* [[Andrej Mangold]] \u2013 German basketball player\n* [[Andrew Marr]] \u2013 broadcaster\n* [[Andrew Marvell]] \u2013 poet\n* [[Andrew McCullough]] \u2013 Australian Rugby League player\n* [[Andrew McCutchen]] \u2013 American baseball player\n* [[Andrew Mehrtens]] \u2013 rugby union player\n* [[Andrew Mellon]] \u2013 American businessman, philanthropist and politician\n* [[Andrew Micallef]] \u2013 Maltese painter and musician\n* [[Andrew Miller (disambiguation)|Andrew Miller]]\n* [[Andy Murray (tennis player)|Andrew Murray]] \u2013 tennis player\n* [[Andrew Neil]] \u2013 political journalist and broadcaster\n* [[Andrew O'Keefe]] \u2014 Australian TV personality\n* [[Andrew Provence]] \u2013 American football player\n* [[Andrew Raycroft]] \u2013 ice hockey player\n* [[Andy Richter]] \u2013 actor/writer/comedian\n* [[Andrew Ridgeley]] \u2013 English musician, [[George Michael]]'s partner in [[Wham!]]\n* [[Andrew Robertson]] - Scottish football player\n* [[Andrew Robinson (water polo)|Andrew Robinson]] \u2013 water polo player\n* [[Andrew Sabiston]] \u2014 Canadian voice actor\n* [[Andrew Sachs]] \u2013 character actor\n* [[Andrew Sega]] \u2013 American musician\n* [[Andy Shernoff|Andrew \"Andy\" Shernoff]] \u2013 songwriter/guitarist for the pre-punk band [[The Dictators]]\n* [[Andrew Shue]] \u2013 American actor\n* [[Andrew Stahl]] \u2013 television and film actor\n* [[Andrew Stanton]] \u2013 \"Pixar\" producer, director, voice actor, and screenwriter\n* [[Andrew Stevovich]] \u2013 American visual artist\n* [[Andrew Stockdale]] \u2013 guitarist and singer of [[Wolfmother]]\n* [[Andrew Symonds]] \u2013 cricketer\n* [[Andrew Sznajder]] (born 1967) \u2013 English-born Canadian tennis player\n* [[Andrew Tanenbaum]] \u2013 computer scientist\n* [[Andrew Tiller]] (born 1989) \u2013 American football player\n* [[Andrew Timlin]] \u2013 field hockey player\n* [[Andrew Toney]] \u2013 basketball player\n* [[Andrew Van Ginkel]] (born 1997) \u2013 American football player\n* [[Andy Van Slyke]] \u2013 baseball player\n* [[Andrew VanWyngarden]] \u2013 musician\n* [[Andrew Vaughn (baseball)|Andrew Vaughn]] (born 1998), American professional baseball player\n* [[Andrew Vollert]] (born 1995) \u2013 American football player\n* [[Andrew W.K.]] \u2013 American singer-songwriter, multi-instrumentalist, entertainer, and motivational speaker\n* [[Andrew Wade]] \u2013 American sound engineer and producer\n* [[Andrew Wagner]] \u2013 American film director\n* [[Andrew Walter]] \u2013 American football player\n* [[Andy Warhol]] \u2013  American pop artist\n* [[Andrew West (disambiguation)]], several people\n* [[Andrew Wiles]] \u2013 British mathematician, proved Fermat's Last Theorem\n* [[Andrew Wiggins]] \u2013 Canadian basketball player\n* [[Andrew Wingard]] (born 1996) \u2013 American football player\n* [[Andrew Wood (singer)|Andrew Wood]] \u2013 singer for grunge band [[Mother Love Bone]]\n* [[Andrew Wyeth]] \u2013 American visual artist\n* [[Andrew Yang]] - American entrepreneur, philanthropist, lawyer, and 2020 presidential candidate\n\n=== Religion ===\n* [[Andrew Kumarage]] \u2013 3rd Anglican [[Bishop of Kurunegala]]\n\n===Other===\n*[[Andrew Cunanan]] (1969-1997), Filipino-American serial killer \n\n=== In fiction ===\n* Andrew Glouberman, character from ''[[Big Mouth (TV series)|Big Mouth]]''\n* Andrew, angel of death from ''[[Touched by an Angel]]''\n* Andrew, robot from [[Isaac Asimov]]'s 1976 novella ''[[The Bicentennial Man]]'' and its [[Bicentennial Man (film)|1999 film adaptation]]\n*Andrew Beckett from the film [[Philadelphia (film)|Philadelphia]]\n* [[List of Weeds characters#Andy Botwin|Andy Botwin]] from the TV series ''[[Weeds (TV series)|Weeds]]''\n* [[Andy Bernard]] from the TV series ''[[The Office (U.S. TV series)|The Office]]''\n* Andy Davis, character from Disney Pixar's ''[[Toy Story]]'' and its sequels\n* Andy Dufresne, from the [[Stephen King]] novel ''[[Rita Hayworth and Shawshank Redemption]]'' and the film adaption ''[[The Shawshank Redemption]]''\n* [[Andrew Ryan (BioShock)|Andrew Ryan]] from the video game ''[[BioShock]]''\n* Drew Torres, from ''[[Degrassi: The Next Generation]]''\n* [[Ender Wiggin|Andrew Wiggin]] aka [[Ender Wiggin]], the title character from [[Orson Scott Card]]'s famous science fiction novel ''[[Ender's Game]]''\n* [[Andrei Nikolayevich Bolkonsky]], central character in [[Leo Tolstoy]]'s novel ''[[War and Peace]]''\n* [[Andy Dwyer]], a character from the TV series ''[[Parks and Recreation]]''\n* Andrew Fillier, a character in the film ''[[Cyberbully (2011 film)|Cyberbully]]''\n* Andrew Hanbridge, a character in the anime series ''[[Little Witch Academia]]''\n\n==See also==<!-- PLESE RESPECT ALPHABETICAL ORDER -->\n* {{lookfrom|Andrew}}\n* {{lookfrom|Andy}}\n* {{lookfrom|Drew}}\n* [[Andy (given name)]]\n* [[Andr\u00e9|Andre (disambiguation)]]\n* [[Andrea]]\n* [[Andreas]]\n* [[Andreou]]\n* [[Andrey]]\n* [[Andrew (surname)]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n{{Given name}}\n\n[[Category:English masculine given names]]\n[[Category:Given names of Greek language origin]]\n", "text_old": "{{other uses}}\n{{Infobox given name\n| name                 = Andrew\n| image                = Andreas San Giovanni in Laterano 2006-09-07.jpg\n| image_size           = \n| caption              = [[Andrew the Apostle|Saint Andrew]]\n| pronunciation        = {{IPAc-en|\u02c8|\u00e6|n|d|r|u\u02d0}}\n| gender               = [[Male]]\n| meaning              = manly and strong<ref name=\"etymonline\">{{cite web |url=http://www.etymonline.com/index.php?term=Andrew |title=Online Etymology Dictionary |work=etymonline.com}}</ref><ref name=\"behind the name\">{{cite web |url=http://www.behindthename.com/name/andrew |title=Behind the Name: Meaning, Origin and History of the Name Andrew |author=Mike Campbell |work=Behind the Name}}</ref>\n| name day             = [[November 30]]\n| region               = [[Greece]]\n| languageorigin       = [[Greek language|Greek]]\n| seealso              = [[Ander]], [[Anders]], [[Andy (given name)|Andy]], [[Andre (given name)|Andre]], [[Andrei (given name)|Andrei]], [[Andrejs]], [[Andrzej (disambiguation)|Andrzej]], [[Andriy]], [[Andrea]], [[Andreas]], [[Andrey]], [[Andrej]], [[Andres (name)|Andres]]\n}}\n\n'''Andrew''' is the English form of a [[given name]] common in many countries. In the 1990s, it was among the top ten most popular names given to boys in [[List of countries where English is an official language|English-speaking countries]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.babycenter.com/babyname/names90.html |title=BabyCenter 1990s \u2013 Most Popular Names}}</ref>  \"Andrew\" is frequently shortened to \"Andy\" or \"Drew\". The word is derived from the {{lang-el|\u1f08\u03bd\u03b4\u03c1\u03ad\u03b1\u03c2}}, ''[[Andreas]]'',<ref name=\"urlOnline Etymology Dictionary\">{{cite web |url=http://etymonline.com/index.php?term=Andrew |title=Online Etymology Dictionary |format= |work= |accessdate=2 December 2011}}</ref> itself related to {{lang-grc|\u1f00\u03bd\u03ae\u03c1/\u1f00\u03bd\u03b4\u03c1\u03cc\u03c2}} ''aner/andros'', \"man\" (as opposed to \"woman\"), thus meaning \"manly\" and, as consequence, \"brave\", \"strong\", \"courageous\", and \"warrior\". In the [[King James Version|King James Bible]], the Greek \"\u1f08\u03bd\u03b4\u03c1\u03ad\u03b1\u03c2\" is translated as Andrew.<ref name=\"urlBible Concordance: Andrew\">{{cite web |url=http://concordances.org/a/andrew.htm |title=Bible Concordance: Andrew |accessdate=2 December 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121008063719/http://concordances.org/a/andrew.htm |archivedate=8 October 2012}}</ref>\n\n== Popularity ==\n\n=== Australia ===\nIn 2000, the name Andrew was the second most popular name in Australia.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.babynames.com.au/Search/search-categories-popular-list.asp?Year=1990&Gender=Boys |title=Popular names, 1990s |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061005221933/http://www.babynames.com.au/Search/search-categories-popular-list.asp?Year=1990&Gender=Boys |archivedate=October 5, 2006}}</ref> In 1999, it was the 19th most common name,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.babynames.com.au/Search/search-categories-popular-list.asp?Year=1980&Gender=Boys |title=Popular names, 1980s |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060927173454/http://www.babynames.com.au/Search/search-categories-popular-list.asp?Year=1980&Gender=Boys |archivedate=September 27, 2006}}</ref> while in 1940, it was the 31st most common name.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.babynames.com.au/Search/search-categories-popular-list.asp?Year=1970&Gender=Boys |title=Popular names, 1970s |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061005221515/http://www.babynames.com.au/Search/search-categories-popular-list.asp?Year=1970&Gender=Boys |archivedate=October 5, 2006}}</ref> Andrew was the first most popular name given to boys in the Northern Territory in 2003 to 2015 and continuing.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nt.gov.au/justice/graphpages/bdm/popnames.shtml |title=Births, Deaths & Marriages (Most Popular Names) \u2013 Northern Territory Department of Justice \u2013 Australia |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070312155853/http://www.nt.gov.au/justice/graphpages/bdm/popnames.shtml |archivedate=March 12, 2007}}</ref> In Victoria, Andrew was the first most popular name for a boy in the 1970s.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://baby2see.com/names/australian_baby_boys_names.html |title=Most Popular Boys Baby Names in Australia}}</ref>\n\n=== Canada ===\nAndrew was the 20th most popular name chosen for male infants in 2005.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.todaysparent.com/pregnancybirth/becomingparent/article.jsp?content=20050617_144619_5504&page=1 |title=Top 100 Baby Names in Canada |publisher=Today's Parent |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070904041213/http://www.todaysparent.com/pregnancybirth/becomingparent/article.jsp?content=20050617_144619_5504&page=1 |archivedate=2007-09-04}}</ref>\nAndrew was the 16th most popular name for infants in British Columbia in 2004,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vs.gov.bc.ca/babynames/baby2004.html |title=BC Vital Statistics Agency (2004) |publisher=British Columbia Ministry of Health |access-date=2007-04-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070427125603/http://www.vs.gov.bc.ca/babynames/baby2004.html |archive-date=2007-04-27 |url-status=dead }}</ref> the 17th most popular name in 2003,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vs.gov.bc.ca/babynames/baby2003.html |title=BC Vital Statistics Agency (2003) |publisher=British Columbia Ministry of Health |access-date=2007-04-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070503162309/http://www.vs.gov.bc.ca/babynames/baby2003.html |archive-date=2007-05-03 |url-status=dead }}</ref> and the 19th most popular name in 2002.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vs.gov.bc.ca/babynames/baby2002.html |title=BC Vital Statistics Agency (2002) |publisher=British Columbia Ministry of Health |access-date=2007-04-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070503162355/http://www.vs.gov.bc.ca/babynames/baby2002.html |archive-date=2007-05-03 |url-status=dead }}</ref> In 2001, it was the 18th most common name.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vs.gov.bc.ca/babynames/baby2001.html |title=BC Vital Statistics Agency (2001) |publisher=British Columbia Ministry of Health |access-date=2007-04-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070503162056/http://www.vs.gov.bc.ca/babynames/baby2001.html |archive-date=2007-05-03 |url-status=dead }}</ref> From 1999 to 2003, Andrew was the sixth most often chosen name for a boy.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://baby2see.com/names/canada_babynames.html |title=Most Popular Babies Names in Canada}}</ref>\n\n=== Europe ===\nIn the United Kingdom in 1974, Andrew was the fourth-most common name given to baby boys, and it was third in 1964. In Scotland, Andrew was the most popular name given to baby boys in 1993, with 1,099 boys given the name that year.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.babycenter.ca/pregnancy/naming/topnamespast/ |title=Popular baby names from the past}}</ref>\n\nIn Norway, with the spelling 'Andreas', the name has been the second-most common name given to boys of the 1990s.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ssb.no/navn/topp10/topp50/1990.html |title=Popular boy baby names 1990\u20131999}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! Year\n! England & Wales\n! Ireland\n! Northern Ireland\n! Scotland\n! Norway\n! Poland\n|-\n| 2007 || 99th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ourbabynames.co.uk/ukpopular2007.php |title=Top Baby Names for Boys in England and Wales (2007)}}</ref> || * || * || * || *\n| 19th\n|-\n| 2006 || 97th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/england/2006 |title=Top Baby Names for Boys in England and Wales (2006)}}</ref> || * || * || * || 6th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ssb.no/en/befolkning/statistikker/navn/aar/2015-01-27?fane=tabell&sort=nummer&tabell=215683 |title=Statistics Norway}}</ref>\n| *\n|-\n| 2005 || 86th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/England+and+Wales/2005 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in England and Wales (2005)}}</ref> || 39th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/Ireland/2005 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in Ireland (2005)}}</ref> || * || 16th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/Scotland/2005 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in Scotland (2005)}}</ref> || 8th\n| *\n|-\n| 2004 || 80th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/England+and+Wales/2004 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in England and Wales (2004)}}</ref> || 32nd<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/Ireland/2004 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in Ireland (2004)}}</ref> || * || 16th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/Scotland/2004 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in Scotland (2004)}}</ref> || 4th\n| *\n|-\n| 2003 || 74th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/England+and+Wales/2003 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in England and Wales (2003)}}</ref> || 36th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/Ireland/2003 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in Ireland (2003)}}</ref> || * || 17th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/Scotland/2003 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in Scotland (2003)}}</ref> || 4th\n| *\n|-\n| 2002 || 63rd<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.statistics.gov.uk/specials/babiesnames_boys.asp |title=Top 100 names for baby boys in England and Wales |publisher=National Statistics}}</ref> || 41st<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/Ireland/2002 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in Ireland (2002)}}</ref> || * || 17th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/Scotland/2002 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in Scotland (2002)}}</ref> || 5th\n| *\n|-\n| 2001 || 56th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/England+and+Wales/2001 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in England and Wales (2001)}}</ref> || 37th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/Ireland/2001 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in Ireland (2001)}}</ref> || * || 7th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/Scotland/2001 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in Scotland (2001)}}</ref> || 4th\n| *\n|-\n| 2000 || 53rd<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/England+and+Wales/2000 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in England and Wales (2000)}}</ref> || 31st<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/Ireland/2000 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in Ireland (2000)}}</ref> || * || 6th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/Scotland/2000 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in Scotland (2000)}}</ref> || 7th\n| *\n|-\n| 1999 || 46th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/England+and+Wales/1999 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in England and Wales (1999)}}</ref> || 28th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/Ireland/1999 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in Ireland (1999)}}</ref> || * || 7th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/Scotland/1999 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in Scotland (1999)}}</ref> || 4th\n| *\n|-\n| 1998 || 40th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/England+and+Wales/1998 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in England and Wales (1998)}}</ref> || 23rd<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/Ireland/1998 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in Ireland (1998)}}</ref> || * || 8th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinkbabynames.com/popular/1/Scotland/1998 |title=Top 100 Baby Names for Boys in Scotland (1998)}}</ref> || 5th\n| *\n|-\n| 1997 || * || * || * || * || 1st\n| 10th\n|-\n| 1996 || * || * || * || * || 3rd\n| *\n|-\n| 1995 || * || * || 6th<ref>{{cite web |url=http://baby2see.com/names/topboysnamesscotlandireland.html |title=Most Popular Boys Baby Names in Northern Ireland, Scotland and Wales}}</ref> || * || 2nd\n| *\n|}\n\n=== United States ===\nThe eleventh most common baby name in 2006,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.babycenter.com/general/1506831.html |title=Top 100 Names of 2006}}</ref> Andrew was among the ten most popular names for male infants in 2005.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ssa.gov/OACT/babynames/ |title=Popular baby names |publisher=United States Social Security Administration}}</ref> Andrew was the sixth most popular choice for a male infant in 2004.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.canada.com/topics/lifestyle/parenting/story.html?id=29817ed5-5a13-4297-9e19-e152aa86078b&k=25431 |title=Emily, Jacob remain popular baby names |publisher=[[Canada.com]]}}</ref> In 2002 and 2001, Andrew was the seventh most popular baby name in the United States.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.socialsecurity.gov/pressoffice/pr/baby-names-pr.htm |title=Social Security Administration Delivers Most Popular Baby Names for 2002 |publisher=United States Social Security Administration}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.popularbabynames.com/cgi-bin/show_page.pl?fpage=a_02_babynames |title=Top 10 names of 2002 in USA |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070930105501/http://www.popularbabynames.com/cgi-bin/show_page.pl?fpage=a_02_babynames |archivedate=2007-09-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.popularbabynames.com/cgi-bin/show_page.pl?fpage=a_01_babynames |title=Top 10 names of 2001 in USA |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070930105514/http://www.popularbabynames.com/cgi-bin/show_page.pl?fpage=a_01_babynames |archivedate=2007-09-30}}</ref> In the 1980s, Andrew was the 19th most popular choice of baby name in the United States.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.babycenter.com/babyname/names80.html |title=BabyCenter 1980s \u2013 Most Popular Names}}</ref> In the 1970s it was the 31st most popular name.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.babycenter.com/babyname/names70.html |title=BabyCenter 1970s \u2013 Most Popular Names}}</ref> From the 1960s stretching back at least as far as the 1880s, Andrew was not among the forty most popular names in America.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.babycenter.com/babyname/names60.html |title=BabyCenter 1960s \u2013 Most Popular Names}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.babycenter.com/babyname/names50.html |title=BabyCenter 1950s \u2013 Most Popular Names}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.babycenter.com/babyname/names40.html |title=BabyCenter 1940s \u2013 Most Popular Names}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.babycenter.com/babyname/names30.html |title=BabyCenter 1930s \u2013 Most Popular Names}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.babycenter.com/babyname/names20.html |title=BabyCenter 1920s \u2013 Most Popular Names}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.babycenter.com/babyname/names10.html |title=BabyCenter 1910s \u2013 Most Popular Names}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.babycenter.com/babyname/names00.html |title=BabyCenter 1900s \u2013 Most Popular Names}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.babycenter.com/babyname/names1890.html |title=BabyCenter 1890s \u2013 Most Popular Names}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thenewparentsguide.com/most-popular-baby-names-1880.htm |title=Most Popular Baby Names for Boys and Girls in the 1880s |publisher=the New Parents' Guide |access-date=2007-04-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20020614124128/http://www.thenewparentsguide.com/most-popular-baby-names-1880.htm |archive-date=2002-06-14 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n== Variants by language ==\n* \u0d05\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d2f\u0d4b\u0d38\u0d4d: [[Malayalam language|Malayalam]], masculine\n* Andria: [[Georgian language|Georgian]], masculine\n* Aindrea, [[Aindreas]] or Anndra: [[Scottish Gaelic]], masculine\n* Aindr\u00e9as, Aindri\u00fa, Aindreas: [[Irish Gaelic]], masculine\n* [[Anaru (name)|Anaru]]: Maori, masculine\n* Andra: [[Scots language|Scots]], masculine\n* [[Ander]]: [[Basque language|Basque]], masculine\n* [[Anders]]: [[Danish language|Danish]], [[Finnish language|Finnish]], [[German language|German]], [[Norwegian language|Norwegian]], [[Swedish language|Swedish]]\n* [[Andras]]: [[Welsh language|Welsh]]\n* [[Andr\u00e1s]], [[Endre (disambiguation)|Endre]]: [[Hungarian language|Hungarian]], masculine\n* [[Andra\u0161]]: [[Prekmurje dialect]] of Slovene, masculine\n* [[Andra\u017e]]: [[Slovene language|Slovene]], masculine\n* [[Andr\u00e9]] or Andre: [[French language|French]] and [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]], masculine\n* [[Andrea]]: [[Albanian language|Albanian]], [[Italian language|Italian]], [[Latin language|Latin]], masculine; [[Croatian language|Croatian]], [[Czech language|Czech]], [[Danish language|Danish]], [[English language|English]], [[Finnish language|Finnish]], [[Galician language|Galician]], [[German language|German]], [[Hungarian language|Hungarian]], [[Icelandic language|Icelandic]], [[Macedonian language|Macedonian]], [[Norwegian language|Norwegian]], [[Slovak language|Slovak]], [[Spanish language|Spanish]], [[Swedish language|Swedish]], feminine\n* [[Andreas]]: [[Armenian language|Armenian]], [[Cypriot Greek]], [[Danish language|Danish]], [[German language|German]], [[Greek language|Greek]], [[Norwegian language|Norwegian]], [[Icelandic language|Icelandic]], [[Swedish language|Swedish]], [[Welsh Language|Welsh]], masculine\n* [[Andreu (disambiguation)|Andreu]]: [[Catalan language|Catalan]], masculine\n* [[Andreea]]: [[Romanian language|Romanian]], feminine\n* [[Andr\u00e9e (given name)|Andr\u00e9e]]: [[French language|French]], feminine\n* [[Andrees]]: Older [[Dutch language|Dutch]] and seldom used [[Afrikaans]], masculine\n* [[Andrei (given name)|Andrei]]: [[Moldovan language|Moldovan]], [[Romanian language|Romanian]], [[Belarusian language|Belarusian]], [[Russian language|Russian]], masculine\n* [[Andreia]]: [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]], feminine\n* [[Andreina]]: [[Italian language|Italian]], feminine\n* [[Andris]]: [[Latvian language|Latvian]], masculine\n* [[Andrei (given name)|Andrei]]: [[Romanian language|Romanian]], masculine\n* [[Andrej]]: [[Belarusian language|Belarusian]], [[Croatian language|Croatian]], [[Macedonian language|Macedonian]], [[Serbian language|Serbian]], [[Slovak language|Slovak]], [[Slovene language|Slovene]], masculine\n* [[Andrey]]: [[Russian language|Russian]] and [[Bulgarian language|Bulgarian]], masculine (Cyrillic and thus often alternatively transliterated as Andrei for both)\n* [[Andreja]]: [[Macedonian language|Macedonian]], masculine; [[Croatian language|Croatian]], [[Slovene language|Slovene]], feminine\n* Andreo: [[Spanish language|Spanish]], masculine\n* [[Andres (name)|Andres]]: [[Estonian language|Estonian]], masculine\n* [[Andres (name)|Andr\u00e9s]]: [[Icelandic language|Icelandic]], [[Spanish language|Spanish]], masculine\n* Andressa: [[Brazilian Portuguese language|Portuguese]], feminine\n* Andreu: [[Catalan language|Catalan]], masculine\n* Andrew: [[English language|English]], masculine\n* [[Andric (given name)|Andric]]: [[English language|English]], masculine\n* [[Andries]]: [[Dutch language|Dutch]] and [[Afrikaans]], masculine\n* [[Andri]]: [[Icelandic language|Icelandic]], masculine\n* [[Andrii]]: [[Ukrainian language|Ukrainian]], masculine\n* [[Andrija]]: [[Croatian language|Croatian]] and [[Serbian language|Serbian]], masculine\n* [[Andrijana]]: [[Macedonian language|Macedonian]], [[Serbian language|Serbian]], feminine\n* [[Andris]], [[Andrejs]], An\u017eejs or [[And\u017eejs]]: [[Latvian language|Latvian]], masculine\n* [[Andrius]]: [[Lithuanian language|Lithuanian]], masculine\n* [[Andriy]]: [[Ukrainian language|Ukrainian]], masculine\n* [[Andrzej]] or [[J\u0119drzej]]: [[Polish language|Polish]], masculine\n* [[Andrzeja]]: [[Polish language|Polish]], feminine; obsolete\n* [[Antti]]: [[Finnish language|Finnish]], masculine\n* [[Ond\u0159ej]]: [[Czech language|Czech]], masculine\n* [[Ondrej]] or [[Andrej]]: [[Slovak language|Slovak]], masculine\n* [[Andrij]]: [[Ukrainian language|Ukrainian]], masculine\n* [[Indr\u00ec (name)|Indr\u00ec]] or [[Andrija]]: [[Maltese language|Maltese]], masculine\n* Andis, Andijs or Endijs: [[Latvian language|Latvian]], masculine\n* In [[Albanian language|Albanian]]: [[Andrea]], Andreu, Andr\u00e9, Ndr\u00e9, Ndreu, And\u00ebr, And\u00ebrs, masculine\n* \uc564\ub4dc\ub958: [[Korean language|Korean]], masculine\n* \u30a2\u30f3\u30c7\u30eb\u30fc: [[Japanese language|Japanese]], masculine\n* \u5b89\u5fb7\u9c81: [[Mandarin Chinese]] (simplified), masculine\n* \u5b89\u5fb7\u9b6f: [[Mandarin Chinese]] (traditional), masculine\n* \u0623\u0646\u062f\u0631\u0627\u0648\u0633 \"Andar\u0101wus\": [[Arabic language|Arabic]], masculine (or \u0623\u0646\u062f\u0631\u064a\u0647 \"Andrayh\" from French, or \u0623\u0646\u062f\u0631\u0648 \"Andr\u016b\" from English)\n* \u12a5\u1295\u12f5\u122a\u12eb\u1235: [[Amharic language|Amharic]], masculine\n''For alternate forms of Anna, see [[Anna (name)#Variant forms]]''\n\n== Notable people named Andrew ==\n=== Saint Andrew ===\nIn the Christian [[Bible]], [[Andrew the Apostle|Saint Andrew]] was the earliest disciple of [[Jesus]] and one of the twelve [[Apostles]].\n[[File:Apostol-Andrey-Pervozvannyj.jpg|right|120px|Saint Andrew]]\n\nOther saints named Andrew include:\n* Saint [[Andrew of Trier]] (d. 235), Bishop of Trier\n* Saint [[Andrew of Crete]], an 8th-century archbishop, theologian, homilist, and hymnographer\n* Saint [[Andrew of Crete (martyr)]]\n* Saint [[Andrew of Constantinople]]\n* Saints [[Andrew Dung-Lac]] An Tran, Andrew Thong Kim Nguyen, Andrew Trong Van Tram, and Andrew Tuong of the [[Vietnamese Martyrs]]\n* Saint [[Andrew Kim Taegon]] of the [[Korean Martyrs]]\n\n=== Kings Andrew ===\n* King [[Andrew I of Hungary]]\n* King [[Andrew II of Hungary]]\n* King [[Andrew III of Hungary]]\n\n=== Dukes Andrew ===\n* [[Andrius Algirdaitis]] (1325\u20131399), first son of [[Algirdas]]\n\n=== Princes Andrew ===\n* [[Prince Andrew, Duke of York]] (1960\u2013), second son of [[Elizabeth II of the United Kingdom|Elizabeth II]]\n* [[Prince Andrew of Greece and Denmark]] (1882\u20131944), the aforementioned's paternal grandfather and namesake\n* [[Edward VIII of the United Kingdom|Edward VIII]] (1894\u20131972) bore the name Andrew\n\n=== United States politics ===\n* [[Andrew Cuomo]] (56th Governor of New York)\n* [[Andrew Gillum]] (125th Mayor of Tallahassee, Florida)\n* [[Andrew Jackson]] (7th President of the United States of America)\n* [[Andrew Johnson]] (17th President of the United States of America)\n\n=== Business, culture, science, and sport ===\n* [[Andrew Abercromby]] \u2013 Scottish biomedical engineer and aquanaut\n* [[Andrew Bayes]] \u2013 American football player\n* [[Andrew Benintendi]] \u2013 Baseball player on the Boston Red Sox\n* [[Andy Biersack]] \u2013 lead vocalist of American rock band [[Black Veil Brides]]\n* [[Andrew Bayer]] \u2013 American DJ and Grammy-nominated record producer\n* [[Andrew Beck (American football)|Andrew Beck]] (born 1996) \u2013 American football player\n* [[Andrew Bird]] \u2013  American musician\n* [[Andrew Bloom]] \u2013 American Olympic shot putter\n* [[Andrew Bogut]] \u2013 Australian basketball player\n* [[Andrew Brown (American football)|Andrew Brown]] \u2013 American football player\n* [[Andrew Brunette]] \u2013 ice hockey player\n* [[Andrew Buckley (field hockey)|Andrew Buckley]] \u2013 field hockey player\n* [[Andrew Bynum]] \u2013 basketball player\n* [[Andrew Campbell (outfielder)]] - Australian professional baseball player\n* [[Andrew Carnegie]] \u2013 steel magnate and philanthropist\n* [[Andrew Colvin]] \u2013 Aussie police man and commissioner\n* [[Andrew Craig]] \u2013 keyboardist for The Nightrain\n* [[Andrew Dice Clay]] \u2013 comedian\n* [[Andrew Dost]] \u2013 Guitarist\n* [[Andrew Clayton]] \u2013 freestyle swimmer\n* [[Andrew Cole]] \u2013 footballer\n* [[Andrew Davenport]] (born 1965) \u2013 English actor, puppeteer, voice actor, music composer\n* [[Andrew Davies (writer)|Andrew Davies]] \u2013 screenwriter\n* [[Andy Dawson]] (born 1978) \u2013 English footballer\n* [[Andy Dawson (footballer, born 1979)|Andy Dawson]] (born 1979) \u2013 English footballer\n* [[Andrew De Silva]] (born 1974) \u2013 Sri Lankan Australian rock vocalist\n* [[Andrew Digby]] \u2014 an astronomer and ecologist whose work focusses on resea